      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Topic and a partition\n\nA topic is a logical grouping of messages. \nA partition is a physical grouping of messages. \nA topic can have multiple partitions, and each partition can be on a different broker. \nTopics are just a way to organize your data, while partitions are a way to scale your data.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Topic and a partition\n\nA topic is a logical grouping of messages. \nA partition is a physical grouping of messages. \nA topic can have multiple partitions, and each partition can be on a different broker. \nTopics are just a way to organize your data, while partitions are a way to scale your data.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
